# Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
SERVER_INSTANCE_ID=srv-main

# Client URL (for CORS)
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Redis Configuration (optional - for scaling)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Google Identity Services (GSI) Credentials
# Get these from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# IMPORTANT: You only need the Client ID (not the Client Secret)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ====================================================
# HOW TO GET GOOGLE CREDENTIALS
# ====================================================
# 
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com
# 
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 
# 3. Enable APIs:
#    - Navigate to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
#    - Search and enable "Google Calendar API"
#    - Search and enable "Google+ API" (for user info)
# 
# 4. Configure OAuth Consent Screen:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "OAuth consent screen"
#    - Choose "External" (or "Internal" if G Suite)
#    - Fill in App Name: "Elexico AI"
#    - Add your email as developer contact
#    - Add Scopes:
#      * openid
#      * https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.email
#      * https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.profile
#      * https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.events
# 
# 5. Create OAuth 2.0 Credentials:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - Application type: "Web application"
#    - Name: "Elexico AI Web Client"
#    - Authorized JavaScript origins:
#      * http://localhost:5173
#      * http://localhost:3001
#      * Your production domain (e.g., https://elexico.ai)
#    - Authorized redirect URIs:
#      * http://localhost:3001/auth/callback/google
#      * Your production callback URL
# 
# 6. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to this .env file
# 
# 7. For production, update:
#    - CLIENT_URL to your production frontend URL
#    - GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI to your production callback URL
#    - Add production URLs to Google Console's authorized origins/redirects
# 
# ====================================================
# PRODUCTION NOTES
# ====================================================
# 
# - Use environment variables or secret management (AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
# - Never commit .env file to version control
# - Use HTTPS for all production URLs
# - Consider implementing a proper database for token storage
# - Add rate limiting and security headers
# - Monitor API quotas in Google Cloud Console
